episodes.title: Nisemono no Iji! Kokoro no Hanrangun Kamyu!
episodes.plot: Straw Hat crew helps Vivi testing a group of men pretending to be Rebel Army who guard a small village.

episodes.title: Hanrangun Senshi Kouza! Vivi ni Chikatta Yume!
episodes.plot: Luffy and crew take a break for lunch in the desert, and Vivi reveals her past with Kohza, the leader of the Rebel Army.

episodes.title: Kagerou no Kettou! Ace vs Otoko Scorpion
episodes.plot: Ace pursues a bounty hunter who claims he has defeated Blackbeard, only to find that it is a total lie. Ace concludes that Blackbeard isn't in Alabasta and leaves Luffy's crew.

episodes.title: Iseki to Mayoigo! Vivi to Nakama to Kuni no Katachi
episodes.plot: Luffy, Zoro, and Chopper get lost in the desert.

episodes.title: Spiders Cafe ni 8-ji Teki Kanbu Shuugou
episodes.plot: Baroke Work's teams 1,2, and 4 meet at the Spider's Cafe to await for the meeting with Mr 0. They are carried to the Rain Dinner casino where Crocodile reveals his identity. Meanwhile, Luffy's crew meets with Toto, Kohza's father.

episodes.title: Luffy Tai Vivi! Nakama ni Kakeru Namida no Chikai
episodes.plot: Luffy and Vivi fight against each other when Luffy says that Vivi's idea to stop the rebellion is naive and the only way to solve the problem in Arabasta is by defeating the Crocodile.

episodes.title: Alabasta Sensen! Yume no Machi Rainbase
episodes.plot: Instead of trying to stop the Rebel Army to war against the kingdom's Army, Straw Hat's crew decides to go after Crocodile at Rainbase, only to meet with Smoker and Tashigi once more and fall right into Crocodile's trap.

episodes.title: Zettai Zetsumei no Wana! Rain Dinners Totsunyuu
episodes.plot: Most of Straw Hat's crew is trapped along with Smoker by Crocodile. Vivi and a royal guardian, Pell, fight against Miss All Sunday.

episodes.title: Utopia Sakusen Hatsudou! Ugokidashita Uneri
episodes.plot: Operation Utopia is set into motion. With his devil fruit's ability, Mr. 2 impersonates King Cobra and orders the destruction of Nanohana. Enraged, Rebel Army begins to move.

episodes.title: Kyoufu no Bananawani to Mr. Prince
episodes.plot: Vivi tries desperately to get the key of the cage that traps most of Craw Hat crew from the humongous crocodiles known as Bananawani. Meanwhile, someone contacts Crocodile and introduces himself as Mr. Prince.

episodes.title: Nami Tamashii no Sakebi! Mugiwara no Luffy Fukkatsu!
episodes.plot: Nami and Chopper find Luffy and Zoro and struggle to rescue them. Zoro recovers his Sandai Kitetsu and breaks the chimney, while Luffy tears two buildings apart. The crew is gathered and Nami reveals the truth about Robin.

episodes.title: Mou Hitotsu no Umi Ressha! Rocketman Shutsugeki
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Crew goes to an abandoned warehouse where old Kokoro shows them another train, the Rocket Man. They find Iceburg, who has been setting it up, and depart to chase the Umi Ressha.

episodes.title: Nakama o Sukue! Tekidoushi ga Musunda Chikai no Kizuna!
episodes.plot: The Franky Family joins the Straw Hat pirates when the Rocket Man is leaving the city, and in the way Pauly and two more shipwrights appear in the train. Tree teams must work together to defeat CP9.

episodes.title: Nami o Kudake! Luffy to Zoro no Saikyou Combo
episodes.plot: In order to avoid the dangerous wave that's coming ahead, Luffy and Zoro join their forces. Sanji and Franky are decided to go after Robin but Usopp considers that it's not his duty. In exchange, a mysterious hero appears.

episodes.title: Nazo no Otoko Toujou!? Sono Na wa Sogeking!
episodes.plot: Sanji, Franky and mysterious Sogeking mock T-Bone and his men and release their wagon, leaving them behind. The friends meet master Okama Kempo and Sanji bid them to move forward.

episodes.title: Kokku Taiketsu! Sanji vs Ramen Kenpou
episodes.plot: Sanji is forced to use his hands in the battle against chef Ramen Kempo, who has build himself a noodle armor. The Straw Hat chef uses knifes in order to defeat him.

episodes.title: Yane no Ue no Kettou! Franky VS Nero
episodes.plot: Cybor man Franky is in danger when new CP9 agent Nero discovers his weak point. He adopts a centaur shape and beats him against the train's roof.

episodes.title: Gekitotsu! Onigiri Zoro VS Funekiri T-Bone
episodes.plot: The Rocket Man and his people spots a halved Sea King and Zoro decides to fight against the responsible. T-Bone is running through Umi Ressha rails towards Puffing Tom when he sees the light coming towards him.

episodes.title: Robin Soudatsusen! Sogeking no Kisaku!!
episodes.plot: The Rocket Man meet a strange toad in the middle of the road, while Sanji, Franky and Sogeking manage to take Robin and split the wagons. Robin insists upon going to Enies Lobby but Sanji begs her to return with the crew.

episodes.title: Shihou no shima! Enies Lobby!
episodes.plot: The Rocket Man train is diverted from the rails due to Yokozuna's rage but old Kokoro calms him and the Kaeru joins the crew. Franky Family finds Sanji and Sogeking. Puffing Tom arrives to Enies Lobby.

episodes.title: Jouriku Sakusen Shidou! Mugiwara Ichimi Totsunyuu Seyo!
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat pirates, Franky Family, Galley-La shipwrights and Sogeking prepare their strategy to land in Enies Lobby, but Luffy can't wait and rushes on his own. The battles commences sooner than expected.

episodes.title: Luffy Kaishingeki! Shihou no Shima de Daikessen!!
episodes.plot: The Franky Family along with the shipwrights manage to open the first gate and make it to the main entrance though two brother giants, Oimo and Kashi, stop them. The Straw Hat crew is waiting and Luffy has an army in front of him.

episodes.title: Kyojinzoku to no Koubou! Daini no Tobira o Akero!
episodes.plot: Kashi the giant is defeated when the King Bulls arrive to the main entrance and only Oimo is left. Luffy avoids unnecessary fight with the marines and heads to the Headquarters. The Straw Hat crew's time has come.

episodes.title: Katsuro o Hirake! Sora o Tobu Rocketman!
episodes.plot: The main team has arrived. Bending the outside fence of the island inward, Rocketman uses it as a ramp and flies through the first and second gates.

episodes.title: Luffy ni Oitsuke! Mugiwara Ichimi Souryokusen
episodes.plot: Straw Hat Pirates and ally engage into battles everywhere on the main island while they are trying to catch up with Luffy.

episodes.title: Uragirareta Robin! Sekai Seifu no Omowaku!
episodes.plot: Spandam plans on taking the Straw Hat Pirates prisoner despite his agreement with Robin to leave Straw Hat Pirates alone if she surrenders herself to the government.

episodes.title: Robin o Kaese! Luffy VS Blueno!
episodes.plot: Luffy slingshots himself to the top part of the courthouse, where Blueno stands waiting for him.

episodes.title: Tachidomaru na! Hangeki no Noroshi o Agero!
episodes.plot: Luffy fights against Blueno in the Palace's roof while the Straw Hat Crew receives help from Sogeking and the giants. CP9 agents Kaku and Califa are congratulated with two Akuma No Mi.

episodes.title: Luffy Mokuzen! Saibansho Mae hiroba e Shuuketsu Seyo
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Crew arrives to the foot of the main gate, on the roof of which Luffy is fighting with Blueno. In order to protect his nakama, the captain unravels new amazing abilities.

episodes.title: Subete wa Nakama o Mamoru Tame ni! Gear Second Hatsudou
episodes.plot: Nami, Zoro, Chopper and Sanji are approaching the main island's limit and the Franky crew must pull down the levers of the bridge. Luffy demonstrates his strength and Robin hears him approach.

episodes.title: Kotaero Robin! Mugiwara Ichimi no Sakebi!!
episodes.plot: Zoro gets lost in the palace and decides to open a hole in the ceiling. His attack draws Nami and Chopper with it and together they get to the roof. Sanji kicks his way up and Sogeking is thrown by Kashi. The gang reunites again.

episodes.title: Robin no Kako! Akuma to Yobareta Shoujo!
episodes.plot: CP9 boss Spandam threatens Robin with the Buster Call and her sorrowful memories arise. As a girl, always disrespected by her people, she met Saul the giant, who awakes laugh in her. 4 days later, a mysterious visit arrives.

episodes.title: Shukumei no Oyako! Sono Haha no Na wa Orubia!
episodes.plot: Saul realizes he knows Robin's mother and warns her about the imminent danger. Olvia talks to the archaeologists and goes after 20-year-ago CP9 captain. The world government sets the ancient library on fire and Saul runs to take Robin with him.

episodes.title: Ohara no Higeki! Buster Call no Kyoufu
episodes.plot: The Ohara archaeologists tell their theory about what they think that happened during the Lost Century. The Buster Call is summoned and the Tree of Knowledge is set on fire. Robin is rescued by Saul, the ex vice admiral.

episodes.title: Ikitai to Ie! Oretachi wa Nakama Da!!
episodes.plot: Since she was 8, Robin's life has been a constant struggle to survive. Everybody has told her that her existence was a crime, and now Luffy begs her to stay alive.

episodes.title: Taki ni Mukatte Tobe!! Luffy no Omoi!!
episodes.plot: A summary of Luffy's backstory.

episodes.title: Otoko no Ikizama! Zoro no Waza, Usopp no Yume
episodes.plot: A summary of Zoro and Usopp's backstory.

episodes.title: Namida ga Tsumuida Nakama no Kizuna! Nami no Sekai Chizu
episodes.plot: A summary of Nami's backstory.

episodes.title: Wakare ga Otoko o Migaku! Sanji to Chopper
episodes.plot: A summary of Sanji and Chopper's backstory.

episodes.title: Subete wa Nakama no Tame ni! Yami no Naka no Robin!
episodes.plot: A summary of Robin's backstory, as well as the reasons of her recent actions.

episodes.title: Sekkeizu wa Watasanai! Franky no Ketsudan
episodes.plot: Franky decides to burn the blueprint he holds all this time in front of Spandam. Straw Hat Pirates crosses into the Tower of Law with Rocketman.

episodes.title: Itsutsu no Kagi o Ubae! Mugiwara Ichimi Tai CP9
episodes.plot: The key to open the seastone handcuff on Robin is owned by 5 members of CP9. Thus, each Straw Hat Pirate and Franky engages themselves into battle against CP9. Meanwhile, Spandam and Lucci takes Robin to Gates of Justice through a secret passage.

episodes.title: Akuma no Mi no Chikara! Kaku to Jabra Daihenshin
episodes.plot: Zoro encounters Kaku, while Usopp tries to steal a key from sleeping Jabura. Both are the user of Zoan-type devil fruits, enable Kaku turns into a giraffe and Jabura turns into a wolf.

episodes.title: Shinde mo Keran! Sanji Otoko no Kishidou!
episodes.plot: Sanji encounters Kalifa, and because of his vow to rather die than kick a woman, he is defeated easily. Seeing Sanji being defeated and in a horrible condition, Nami decides to take over and fights against Kalifa.

episodes.title: Fukurou no Gosan! Ore no Cola wa Inochi no Mizu!
episodes.plot: Franky gets into a fist fight with Fukuro.

episodes.title: Zoro Shinwaza Sakuretsu! Katana no Na wa Sogeking?
episodes.plot: Accidentally, Zoro and Usopp get handcuffed together and neither Jabura nor Kaku has the right key to open the handcuff. Thus, Zoro is forced to fight them both by using Usopp as his sword.

episodes.title: Seigyo Funou! Chopper Kindan no Rumble
episodes.plot: Chopper struggles against Kumadori, and he has reached his limit in using Rumble Balls. But it is impossible for him to win without the power given by his Rumble Ball. So Chopper decides to use Rumble Balls once more and goes totally berserk.

episodes.title: Luffy Oyabun Futatabi! Yume ka Utsutsu ka Tomikuji Soudou
episodes.plot: In Grand Jipangu in Edo period, a little girl named Rika takes care of an ill man whom she calls Tot-san. Assuming Rika as the daughter, Buggy the Clown kidnaps her. Luffy comes to rescue her.
